{"title_page": "Akiruno, Tokyo", "text_new": "{{Refimprove|date=May 2016}}\n{{Infobox settlement\n<!-- See Template:Infobox settlement for additional fields and descriptions -->\n| name                    = {{raise|0.2em|Akiruno}}\n| native_name             = {{lower|0.1em|{{nobold|{{lang|ja|\u3042\u304d\u308b\u91ce\u5e02}}}}}}\n| official_name           = \n| native_name_lang        = ja\n| settlement_type         = [[Cities of Japan|City]]\n<!-- images, nickname, motto -->\n| image_skyline           = Akiruno City Hall.JPG\n| imagesize               = \n| image_alt               = \n| image_caption           = Akiruno City Hall\n| image_flag              = Flag of Akiruno, Tokyo.svg\n| flag_alt                = \n| image_seal              = Emblem of Akiruno, Tokyo.svg\n| seal_alt                = \n| image_shield            = \n| shield_alt              = \n| image_blank_emblem      = \n| nickname                = \n| motto                   = \n<!-- maps and coordinates -->\n| image_map               = Akiruno in Tokyo Prefecture Ja.svg\n| map_alt                 = \n| map_caption             = Location of Akiruno in Tokyo\n| pushpin_map             = Japan\n| pushpin_label_position  = <!-- position of the pushpin label: left, right, top, bottom, none -->\n| pushpin_map_alt         = \n| pushpin_map_caption     = &nbsp;\n| coordinates             = {{coord|35|43|44.1|N|139|17|38.7|E|region:JP|display=inline,title}}\n| coor_pinpoint           = <!-- to specify exact location of coordinates (was coor_type) -->\n| coordinates_footnotes   = <!-- for references: use <ref> tags -->\n<!-- location -->\n| subdivision_type        = [[List of sovereign states|Country]]\n| subdivision_name        = Japan\n| subdivision_type1       = [[List of regions of Japan|Region]]\n| subdivision_name1       = [[Kant\u014d region|Kant\u014d]]\n| subdivision_type2       = [[Prefectures of Japan|Prefecture]]\n| subdivision_name2       = [[Tokyo]]\n| subdivision_type3       = \n| subdivision_name3       = \n<!-- established -->\n| established_title       = <!-- Settled -->\n| established_date        = \n| founder                 = \n| named_for               = \n<!-- seat, smaller parts -->\n| seat_type               = <!-- defaults to: Seat -->\n| seat                    = \n<!-- government type, leaders -->\n| government_footnotes    = <!-- for references: use <ref> tags -->\n| leader_party            = \n| leader_title            = [[Mayor]]\n| leader_name             = Toshikazu Sawai (since October 2015)\n| leader_title1           = \n| leader_name1            = <!-- etc., up to leader_title4 / leader_name4 -->\n<!-- display settings  -->\n| total_type              = <!-- to set a non-standard label for total area and population rows -->\n| unit_pref               = <!-- enter: Imperial, to display imperial before metric -->\n<!-- area -->\n| area_magnitude          = <!-- use only to set a special wikilink -->\n| area_footnotes          = <!-- for references: use <ref> tags -->\n| area_total_km2          = 73.47\n| area_land_km2           = \n| area_water_km2          = \n| area_water_percent      = \n| area_note               = \n<!-- elevation -->\n| elevation_footnotes     = <!-- for references: use <ref> tags -->\n| elevation_m             = \n<!-- population -->\n| population_footnotes    = <!-- for references: use <ref> tags -->\n| population_total        = 80464\n| population_as_of        = February 2016\n| population_density_km2  = 1100\n| population_est          = \n| pop_est_as_of           = \n| population_demonym      = <!-- demonym, ie. Liverpudlian for someone from Liverpool -->\n| population_note         = \n<!-- time zone(s) -->\n| timezone1               = [[Japan Standard Time]]\n| utc_offset1             = +9\n| timezone1_DST           = \n| utc_offset1_DST         = \n<!-- postal codes, area code -->\n| postal_code_type        = \n| postal_code             = \n| area_code_type          = <!-- defaults to: Area code(s) -->\n| area_code               = \n<!-- blank fields (section 1) -->\n| blank_name_sec1         = Symbols\n| blank_info_sec1         = &nbsp;\n| blank1_name_sec1        = \u2022 Tree\n| blank1_info_sec1        = [[Osmanthus fragrans|Tea Olive]]\n| blank2_name_sec1        = \u2022 Flower\n| blank2_info_sec1        = [[Chrysanthemum]]\n| blank3_name_sec1        = \u2022 Bird\n| blank3_info_sec1        = [[Japanese wagtail]]\n| blank4_name_sec1        = \n| blank4_info_sec1        = \n| blank5_name_sec1        = \n| blank5_info_sec1        = \n| blank6_name_sec1        = \n| blank6_info_sec1        = \n| blank7_name_sec1        = \n| blank7_info_sec1        = \n<!-- blank fields (section 2) -->\n| blank_name_sec2         = Phone&nbsp;number\n| blank_info_sec2         = 042-558-1111\n| blank1_name_sec2        = Address\n| blank1_info_sec2        = 350 Ninomiya, Akiruno-shi, Tokyo 197-0814\n<!-- website, footnotes -->\n| website                 = {{URL|http://www.city.akiruno.tokyo.jp/}}\n| footnotes               = \n}}\n\n{{Nihongo|'''Akiruno'''|\u3042\u304d\u308b\u91ce\u5e02|Akiruno-shi}} is a [[Cities of Japan|city]] located in the western portion of [[Tokyo Metropolis]], [[Japan]]. {{As of|2016|02|01}}, the city had an estimated [[population]] of 80,464, and a [[population density]] of 1100 persons per km\u00b2. Its total area is {{convert|73.47|sqkm|sqmi}}.<ref>{{official website|www.city.akiruno.tokyo.jp}}{{in lang|ja}}</ref>\n\n==Geography==\nAkiruno is located in the foothills of the Okutama Mountains of western Tokyo, approximately 40-50 kilometers from the center of Tokyo. The [[Aki River]] and Hirai River flow through the city.\n\nBecause of its rich nature and clam un-Tokyo-like surroundings compared to downtown of Tokyo, and its advantage of transportation, 40 minutes from Shinjuku, many tourist choose Akiruno for their weekend vacation. \n\nEspecially Seoto-no-yo Spa is famous for its high quality alkaline spring and it's called \u201cbeautiful skin spa\u201d.\n\nAlso, Akiruno is one of the most popular place for BBQ, biking and hiking. One of the most famous trail running cup, Hasetsune Cup, is held in Akiruno.\n\n<br />\n\n===Surrounding municipalities===\n*[[Tokyo Metropolis]]\n**[[Fussa, Tokyo|Fussa]]\n**[[Hamura, Tokyo|Hamura]]\n**[[\u014cme, Tokyo|\u014cme]]\n**[[Hachioji, Tokyo|Hachioji]]\n**[[Hinode, Tokyo|Hinode]]\n**[[Okutama, Tokyo|Okutama]]\n**[[Hinohara, Tokyo|Hinohara]]\n\n==History==\nThe area of present-day Akiruno was part of ancient [[Musashi Province]]. In the post-[[Meiji Restoration]] cadastral reform of July 22, 1878, the area became part of [[Nishitama District, Tokyo|Nishitama District]] in [[Kanagawa Prefecture]]. The town of Itsukaichi was created on April 1, 1889, with the establishment of municipalities law. Nishitama District was transferred to the administrative control of Tokyo Metropolis on April 1, 1893. Itsukaichi expanded through annexation of neighboring villages in 1918 and 1955. Higashiakiru, Nishiakiru, and Tasai grouped together on April 1, 1955, to form the town of Akigawa, which was elevated to city status on May 5, 1971.  The city of Akiruno was created on September 1, 1995, by the [[Merger and dissolution of municipalities of Japan|merger]] of the city of [[Akigawa, Tokyo|Akigawa]] with the neighboring town of [[Itsukaichi, Tokyo|Itsukaichi]].\n\n==Education==\nAkiruno has ten public and one private elementary schools, six public and one private middle schools and two public and one private high school. There is also one special education school.\n\n==Transportation==\n\n===Railway===\n*[[JR East]] \u2013 [[Itsukaichi Line]]\n**{{STN|Higashi-Akiru}} \u2013 {{STN|Akigawa}} \u2013 {{STN|Musashi-Hikida}} \u2013 {{STN|Musashi-Masuko}} \u2013 {{STN|Musashi-Itsukaichi}}\n\n===Highway===\n*[[Ken-\u014c Expressway]]\n*[[Japan National Route 411|National Route 411]]\n\n==Sister city relations==\n*{{Flagicon|USA}} \u2013 [[Marlborough, Massachusetts]], United States, since November 3, 1998\n\n==References==\n\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n{{Commons category|Akiruno, Tokyo}}\n{{Portal|Tokyo}}\n*[http://www.city.akiruno.tokyo.jp/ Akiruno City Official Website] {{in lang|ja}}\n\n{{Tokyo}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n[[Category:Cities in Tokyo]]\n[[Category:Western Tokyo]]\n[[Category:Akiruno, Tokyo| ]]\n", "text_old": "{{Refimprove|date=May 2016}}\n{{Infobox settlement\n<!-- See Template:Infobox settlement for additional fields and descriptions -->\n| name                    = {{raise|0.2em|Akiruno}}\n| native_name             = {{lower|0.1em|{{nobold|{{lang|ja|\u3042\u304d\u308b\u91ce\u5e02}}}}}}\n| official_name           = \n| native_name_lang        = ja\n| settlement_type         = [[Cities of Japan|City]]\n<!-- images, nickname, motto -->\n| image_skyline           = Akiruno City Hall.JPG\n| imagesize               = \n| image_alt               = \n| image_caption           = Akiruno City Hall\n| image_flag              = Flag of Akiruno, Tokyo.svg\n| flag_alt                = \n| image_seal              = Emblem of Akiruno, Tokyo.svg\n| seal_alt                = \n| image_shield            = \n| shield_alt              = \n| image_blank_emblem      = \n| nickname                = \n| motto                   = \n<!-- maps and coordinates -->\n| image_map               = Akiruno in Tokyo Prefecture Ja.svg\n| map_alt                 = \n| map_caption             = Location of Akiruno in Tokyo\n| pushpin_map             = Japan\n| pushpin_label_position  = <!-- position of the pushpin label: left, right, top, bottom, none -->\n| pushpin_map_alt         = \n| pushpin_map_caption     = &nbsp;\n| coordinates             = {{coord|35|43|44.1|N|139|17|38.7|E|region:JP|display=inline,title}}\n| coor_pinpoint           = <!-- to specify exact location of coordinates (was coor_type) -->\n| coordinates_footnotes   = <!-- for references: use <ref> tags -->\n<!-- location -->\n| subdivision_type        = [[List of sovereign states|Country]]\n| subdivision